This follows the resignations of Krish Naidoo and Vusi Mavuso earlier this month. JOHANNESBURG The Presidency has confirmed its received and accepted the resignation of a third SABC board member, Leah Khumalo with immediate effect. Khumalos resignation follows those of Krish Naidoo and Vusi Mavuso, who quit earlier this month during a presentation to Parliaments portfolio committee. The SABC board has since been rendered redundant while an inquiry into its fitness is being finalised. The Presidencys Bongani Ngqulunga says, President Zuma has received and accepted the resignation of Ms Leah Khumalo, as a member as well as the deputy chairperson of the SABC board. The president has wished Ms Khumalo well in her future endeavours.